[log] bash[81] stdout ### 2. AsyncBase Class
[log] bash[81] stdout **Class Description**: The AsyncBase class is the base class for all asynchronous file operations. It provides the basic functionality for all asynchronous file operations.
[log] bash[81] stdout **Class Definition**:
[log] bash[81] stdout ```python
[log] bash[81] stdout class AsyncBase:
[log] bash[81] stdout     def __init__(self, file, loop, executor):
[log] bash[81] stdout         self._file = file
[log] bash[81] stdout         self._executor = executor
[log] bash[81] stdout         self._ref_loop = loop
[log] bash[81] stdout     @property
[log] bash[81] stdout     def _loop(self):
[log] bash[81] stdout         return self._ref_loop or get_running_loop()
[log] bash[81] stdout     def __aiter__(self):
[log] bash[81] stdout         """We are our own iterator."""
[log] bash[81] stdout         return self
[log] bash[81] stdout     def __repr__(self):
[log] bash[81] stdout         return super().__repr__() + " wrapping " + repr(self._file)
[log] bash[81] stdout     async def __anext__(self):
[log] bash[81] stdout         """Simulate normal file iteration.
[log] bash[81] stdout         Returns:
[log] bash[81] stdout             str: The next line of the file.
[log] bash[81] stdout         Raises:
[log] bash[81] stdout             StopAsyncIteration: If the end of the file is reached.
[log] bash[81] stdout         """
[log] bash[81] stdout ```
