[log] bash[119] stdout     the executor to avoid blocking.
[log] bash[119] stdout     Args:
[log] bash[119] stdout         attr_name: The name of the attribute (method) to delegate.
[log] bash[119] stdout     Returns:
[log] bash[119] stdout         An async method suitable for assignment to the wrapper class.
[log] bash[119] stdout     """
[log] bash[119] stdout     async def method(self, *args, **kwargs):
[log] bash[119] stdout         rolled = await self._check()
[log] bash[119] stdout         if rolled:
[log] bash[119] stdout             loop = self._loop
[log] bash[119] stdout             func = getattr(self._file, attr_name)
